      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISTER MANAGER (3) was impressive at the latest appearance when he came from the back row and scored by more than 13 metres at this circuit and distance. Up in grade but a nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. CLEAR LEFT NZ (7) was a winner at this circuit and distance last month and was good again last week when he drew wider and worked but fought well for a 2.5m third. Draws for a trail and if he gets the gaps has strong claims. WINGMAN LOU (6) made it two wins from the past four outings here when he came from a similar barrier to score by 1.4 metres last week. Player again. UNCLE TIGER (5) draws wider but can be competitive again after he led and stuck on for a respectable second to WINGMAN LOU last week.",
